						               													<description>Lis: Gra Karciana is a card game created based on the comic book &amp;quot;Lis&amp;quot; published by Wydawnictwo Sol Invictus. Its action takes place in the today Poland and derive from such genres as criminal, thriller or superhero.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The are 66 cards in the deck, which will cause the gameplay to be full of twists and turns. On each of them there are illustrations kept in the style of the comic book &amp;quot;Lis&amp;quot;. In the &amp;quot;Lis: Gra Karciana&amp;quot; players will be able to play as one of four comic book characters, which must collect the appropriate goals.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;There are different type of cards: character, goal and action cards. Each player receives 1 character card face down, 1 goal card and 3 action cards. All remaining cards are mixed together and shuffled. In your turn you can do 2 moves from the following ones: draw a card, play an action card, discard 2 cards from your hand to draw 1 card from the discard pile. The card hand limit is 7 cards.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;At any moment if another player is playing an action card, you can block its effect by saying &amp;quot;stop&amp;quot; and discarding one goal card from your hand. Other players can block your &amp;quot;stop&amp;quot; by doing the same.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;You win immediately if at any point you manage to collect 4 out of 5 goal cards matching (giving 3 points) your character. If nobody was able to collect 4 dedicated goal cards, the game ends after the turn of the player which drew the last card from the deck. In this case the players will sum the points gained from the goal cards based on the scoring from their character cards. The player with the biggest score wins.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
